Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:06.357 --> 00:00:07.824
DIANE SOLINGER:
I'm Diane Solinger.

00:00:07.824 --> 00:00:10.070
I'm the manager of
the GooglersGive team.

00:00:10.070 --> 00:00:12.490
We're the team that sits
in people operations,

00:00:12.490 --> 00:00:15.890
HR here at Google, that
works with our employees,

00:00:15.890 --> 00:00:19.120
so all you great Googlers to
help you give and volunteer

00:00:19.120 --> 00:00:21.650
to organizations and
causes that you care about.

00:00:21.650 --> 00:00:25.590
And we our largely known
for a couple big things.

00:00:25.590 --> 00:00:27.970
One is the Googler
Gift Match Program.

00:00:27.970 --> 00:00:30.300
So every Googler
has the opportunity

00:00:30.300 --> 00:00:33.360
to make contributions and have
those matched by Google, up

00:00:33.360 --> 00:00:35.840
to $6,000 per Googler each year.

00:00:35.840 --> 00:00:37.480
So just in case you
didn't know that,

00:00:37.480 --> 00:00:39.910
remember your gift
match benefit.

00:00:39.910 --> 00:00:42.750
Additionally, we have
donations for doers.

00:00:42.750 --> 00:00:47.880
So if you volunteer, every hour
generates $10 in Google support

00:00:47.880 --> 00:00:50.198
to the organization
that you volunteer with,

00:00:50.198 --> 00:00:52.260
up to $2,500 a year.

00:00:52.260 --> 00:00:54.810
And right now you'll see
a couple things happening.

00:00:54.810 --> 00:00:57.820
We also launched disaster
matching campaigns.

00:00:57.820 --> 00:00:59.670
So there's one
going on right now

00:00:59.670 --> 00:01:02.270
to support the flood
relief in India.

00:01:02.270 --> 00:01:04.850
And soon, very soon, maybe
within the next hour even,

00:01:04.850 --> 00:01:09.700
we will have an Ebola relief
disaster campaign going on.

00:01:09.700 --> 00:01:12.060
In that case, Googlers get
an extra $1,000 of gift

00:01:12.060 --> 00:01:14.980
match to support those
organizations that

00:01:14.980 --> 00:01:17.320
are curated and featured
for those campaigns.

00:01:17.320 --> 00:01:22.300
So all those things can be
found at go/googlersgive.

00:01:22.300 --> 00:01:25.010
If you want to request
a match, it's go/give.

00:01:25.010 --> 00:01:29.320
And for disaster relief,
its' go/givehelp.

00:01:29.320 --> 00:01:31.410
So just a little
bit about the team.

00:01:31.410 --> 00:01:33.390
We're a global team, 13 people.

00:01:33.390 --> 00:01:35.426
We rely on ambassadors.

00:01:35.426 --> 00:01:37.620
So anybody interested
in getting more involved

00:01:37.620 --> 00:01:39.280
in helping Googlers
get involved,

00:01:39.280 --> 00:01:41.404
we are looking for
ambassadors to help us.

00:01:41.404 --> 00:01:43.380
We've got about 160
around the world that

00:01:43.380 --> 00:01:46.300
help us implement programs and
design things that make sense

00:01:46.300 --> 00:01:48.240
for their teams or
for their office,

00:01:48.240 --> 00:01:50.670
and join into big
things like this, which

00:01:50.670 --> 00:01:53.940
is the Education
for All Campaign.

00:01:53.940 --> 00:01:57.560
Education for All is
really what it says.

00:01:57.560 --> 00:02:00.520
It's about trying to
help Googlers support

00:02:00.520 --> 00:02:02.540
educational
organizations in ways

00:02:02.540 --> 00:02:03.930
that mean something to them.

00:02:03.930 --> 00:02:05.910
But also to bring us
together as a team,

00:02:05.910 --> 00:02:09.779
as a global group of Googlers,
to support a unified cause

00:02:09.779 --> 00:02:13.160
that we find Googlers
want to rally around.

00:02:13.160 --> 00:02:14.990
Education tends to be
the number one thing

00:02:14.990 --> 00:02:17.170
that Googlers are
interested in supporting.

00:02:17.170 --> 00:02:20.360
And we find sometimes that it's
kind of analysis paralysis.

00:02:20.360 --> 00:02:21.320
What do I do?

00:02:21.320 --> 00:02:23.260
There's so many choices.

00:02:23.260 --> 00:02:24.860
How do I get involved?

00:02:24.860 --> 00:02:26.260
Where should I give?

00:02:26.260 --> 00:02:28.600
So the campaign that's
been pulled together

00:02:28.600 --> 00:02:31.610
is to really kind of bring
some focus in on education

00:02:31.610 --> 00:02:33.485
and provide some
featured organization

00:02:33.485 --> 00:02:36.370
choices for donations,
and local volunteering

00:02:36.370 --> 00:02:38.902
opportunities for
you to get engaged.

00:02:38.902 --> 00:02:41.854
So that is
go/education campaign.

00:02:41.854 --> 00:02:43.639
This is part of the
campaign as well.

00:02:43.639 --> 00:02:45.680
Because we want to shine
a light on organizations

00:02:45.680 --> 00:02:48.410
that provide an education
opportunity for us

00:02:48.410 --> 00:02:51.530
to learn more about education
issues and opportunities to get

00:02:51.530 --> 00:02:52.030
involved.

00:02:52.030 --> 00:02:55.400
So this panel has come
together to address that.

00:02:55.400 --> 00:02:58.730
We're really fortunate to
have wonderful people here

00:02:58.730 --> 00:03:02.160
to talk about two contexts.

00:03:02.160 --> 00:03:04.580
And we're going to lay it
out this way, a little bit

00:03:04.580 --> 00:03:06.690
about what's going on in the US.

00:03:06.690 --> 00:03:08.940
And we'll have two
wonderful people

00:03:08.940 --> 00:03:10.670
involved in that
from DonorsChoose.

00:03:10.670 --> 00:03:13.592
And then we'll talk a
little bit about education

00:03:13.592 --> 00:03:16.510
outside the U.S. And that
will be focused mostly

00:03:16.510 --> 00:03:18.270
on The Philippines.

00:03:18.270 --> 00:03:19.620
We are a global company.

00:03:19.620 --> 00:03:21.250
And people are
interested in both.

00:03:21.250 --> 00:03:24.740
And I think what we'll find
is that, although the U.S. is

00:03:24.740 --> 00:03:27.651
a developed countries, there's a
lot of parallels between what's

00:03:27.651 --> 00:03:29.025
happening in the
developing world

00:03:29.025 --> 00:03:31.310
and what's happening here
with respect to education.

00:03:31.310 --> 00:03:33.600
There's a gap no
matter where you look.

00:03:33.600 --> 00:03:35.545
And I think people
really want to help.

00:03:35.545 --> 00:03:38.480
And that's what we're
here to talk about today.

