00:04:31.307 --> 00:04:32.890
Yeah, so I run product
and engineering

00:04:32.890 --> 00:04:34.650
at DonorsChoose.org.

00:04:34.650 --> 00:04:37.570
And we're website where public
school teachers post their best

00:04:37.570 --> 00:04:40.260
ideas for classroom
projects that their schools

00:04:40.260 --> 00:04:41.740
can't otherwise afford.

00:04:41.740 --> 00:04:44.840
Think of it as like a
Kickstarter for classrooms.

00:04:44.840 --> 00:04:49.354
Folks on the internet help
bring these projects to life.

00:04:49.354 --> 00:04:50.520
Many people don't know this.

00:04:50.520 --> 00:04:52.670
Unlike say an eBay,
or a Kickstarter,

00:04:52.670 --> 00:04:53.930
we don't then send a check.

00:04:53.930 --> 00:04:56.490
We actually fulfill
the project ourselves.

00:04:56.490 --> 00:04:58.380
So if it's resources,
we deliver them.

00:04:58.380 --> 00:05:00.910
If it's a field trip, we
pay the bus company directly

00:05:00.910 --> 00:05:04.681
and help make the
field trip happen.

00:05:04.681 --> 00:05:05.180
It works.

00:05:05.180 --> 00:05:05.755
It's amazing.

00:05:05.755 --> 00:05:07.810
It was founded 14 years
ago by a public school

00:05:07.810 --> 00:05:09.780
teacher in the Bronx.

00:05:09.780 --> 00:05:11.430
And it spread from
his classroom,

00:05:11.430 --> 00:05:14.310
to the rest of the Bronx, to
the rest of New York City.

00:05:14.310 --> 00:05:15.446
It's now nationwide.

00:05:15.446 --> 00:05:18.430
We've done more
than $260 million

00:05:18.430 --> 00:05:21.230
in donations to
classrooms [INAUDIBLE],

00:05:21.230 --> 00:05:24.470
more than 12 million students
on the receiving end.

00:05:24.470 --> 00:05:27.115
More than half of the public
schools in the country

00:05:27.115 --> 00:05:29.700
have a teacher who's
used the website, which

00:05:29.700 --> 00:05:30.679
is kind of staggering.

