00:11:07.000 --> 00:11:09.520
to have the liquidity to
make the whole thing work.

00:11:09.520 --> 00:11:12.750
He had to sort of basically
bribe teachers to use the site.

00:11:12.750 --> 00:11:16.900
Because if a website has never
given a dollar to a classroom,

00:11:16.900 --> 00:11:18.430
why would a teacher
who's so busy

00:11:18.430 --> 00:11:20.850
spend their time putting
a request up there.

00:11:20.850 --> 00:11:24.474
And then he also had
to bring donors there

00:11:24.474 --> 00:11:26.140
with just a couple
projects on the site.

00:11:26.140 --> 00:11:27.800
Saying, well, it's
all about choice,

00:11:27.800 --> 00:11:29.716
But actually there's
only eight projects there

00:11:29.716 --> 00:11:31.522
because we started a month ago.

00:11:31.522 --> 00:11:34.380
So initially, he had to
spend a ton of effort

00:11:34.380 --> 00:11:35.130
making the market.

00:11:35.130 --> 00:11:37.300
And when I joined the
org eight years ago,

00:11:37.300 --> 00:11:39.670
we had staff members
who were focused

00:11:39.670 --> 00:11:42.150
on driving awareness
among teachers.

00:11:42.150 --> 00:11:47.522
And, fortunately, in 2014, we
now have a level of awareness,

00:11:47.522 --> 00:11:49.980
with the exception of maybe
that school and other schools--

00:11:49.980 --> 00:11:50.920
DIANE SOLINGER:
It's a small school.

00:11:50.920 --> 00:11:53.128
OLIVER HURST-HILLER: But we
have a level of awareness

00:11:53.128 --> 00:11:55.310
where the teachers are
coming to our site.

00:11:55.310 --> 00:11:57.768
And they're asking for stuff
that they can't get elsewhere.

00:11:57.768 --> 00:12:01.302
And we're really racing
on the citizen donor side,

00:12:01.302 --> 00:12:02.760
racing to keep up
with that demand,

00:12:02.760 --> 00:12:05.260
and trying to find innovative
ways to get them funding.

00:12:05.260 --> 00:12:07.130
So at this point,
it's essentially

00:12:07.130 --> 00:12:09.037
like a word of mouth thing.

00:12:09.037 --> 00:12:10.870
For example, when you're
on boarded at Teach

00:12:10.870 --> 00:12:13.290
for America, when they take
this recent college grad.

00:12:13.290 --> 00:12:17.570
And they say, hey, you're about
to dive into a challenging

00:12:17.570 --> 00:12:20.500
situation at high needs
school, part of their briefing

00:12:20.500 --> 00:12:22.319
includes DonorsChoose.org
You go here.

00:12:22.319 --> 00:12:24.360
And this is where you get
the resources you need.

00:12:24.360 --> 00:12:28.580
So the good news is that the
word of mouth has taken over.

00:12:28.580 --> 00:12:31.480
And we have a lot of work
to do with Google's help,

00:12:31.480 --> 00:12:33.252
and get those projects funded.

00:12:33.252 --> 00:12:34.960
DIANE SOLINGER: Are
you seeing any trends

00:12:34.960 --> 00:12:36.980
in what teachers are needing?

00:12:36.980 --> 00:12:39.250
