00:13:22.810 --> 00:13:24.470
taught for this
particular curriculum.

00:13:24.470 --> 00:13:25.970
Or it might be a
piece of technology

00:13:25.970 --> 00:13:28.260
which the school's not yet
using in the classroom.

00:13:28.260 --> 00:13:29.676
But they're a
little tech forward.

00:13:29.676 --> 00:13:32.150
And they want to try.

00:13:32.150 --> 00:13:34.150
And it's just, as
you can imagine,

00:13:34.150 --> 00:13:39.180
there isn't a natural
budgeting way in the way

00:13:39.180 --> 00:13:41.066
that schools are
funded today, in terms

00:13:41.066 --> 00:13:42.907
of the district and the
school, for teachers

00:13:42.907 --> 00:13:44.740
to think outside the
box, and they get money

00:13:44.740 --> 00:13:45.910
to think outside the box.

00:13:45.910 --> 00:13:47.610
It's like you're
really just hoping

00:13:47.610 --> 00:13:49.790
you got the money
you got last year.

00:13:49.790 --> 00:13:52.049
And so one of the most
exciting things for us

00:13:52.049 --> 00:13:53.590
is seeing the stuff
on the site where

00:13:53.590 --> 00:13:55.230
the teachers are
being innovative.

00:13:55.230 --> 00:13:56.520
And they're outside the box.

00:13:56.520 --> 00:13:59.060
And they're trying something
new, and taking a risk.

00:13:59.060 --> 00:14:01.050
And then citizen
donors, this person

00:14:01.050 --> 00:14:03.341
hasn't had to go through sort
of the whole bureaucracy,

00:14:03.341 --> 00:14:04.930
and champion an
idea which may fail.

00:14:04.930 --> 00:14:08.210
