00:16:02.520 --> 00:16:04.422
DIANE SOLINGER: He's
a determined guy.

00:16:04.422 --> 00:16:07.050
TIM FERRISS: And we've
kept close for a long time.

00:16:07.050 --> 00:16:09.450
And we share very
similar values.

00:16:09.450 --> 00:16:12.054
And I think that DonorsChoose
shares a lot of similar values

00:16:12.054 --> 00:16:12.856
with most Googlers.

00:16:12.856 --> 00:16:16.965
And I've spent a lot of time
here, and at the Googleplex,

00:16:16.965 --> 00:16:20.830
and with a lot of people
who have worked for Google.

00:16:20.830 --> 00:16:24.120
DonorsChoose for me is
important for a few reasons.

00:16:24.120 --> 00:16:28.530
Number one is, a lot of people
in this room, I suspect,

00:16:28.530 --> 00:16:30.480
feel strongly about education.

00:16:30.480 --> 00:16:31.750
And perhaps you're like me.

00:16:31.750 --> 00:16:34.402
You recognize that there are few
inflection points in your life

00:16:34.402 --> 00:16:35.610
where you had an opportunity.

00:16:35.610 --> 00:16:36.940
You had a particular teacher.

00:16:36.940 --> 00:16:38.148
You had a particular project.

00:16:38.148 --> 00:16:41.470
You had a particular
type of support

00:16:41.470 --> 00:16:43.040
where you could
have gone this way.

00:16:43.040 --> 00:16:44.290
And instead you went this way.

00:16:44.290 --> 00:16:46.775
And for me, that
was especially true

00:16:46.775 --> 00:16:49.730
in second grade, fifth grade,
ninth grade, and tenth grade.

00:16:49.730 --> 00:16:52.980
I remember the exact teachers
and the exact projects.

00:16:52.980 --> 00:16:55.602
And I want to
encourage everybody.

00:16:55.602 --> 00:16:57.560
If you're king about
education, what I realized

00:16:57.560 --> 00:17:00.480
is you can't fix education
any more than you

00:17:00.480 --> 00:17:03.180
can sort of fix violence or war.

00:17:03.180 --> 00:17:04.910
You have to thin slice it.

00:17:04.910 --> 00:17:07.369
And DonorsChoose
allows you to do that.

00:17:07.369 --> 00:17:10.770
So for my case, I care about a
couple of things very deeply.

00:17:10.770 --> 00:17:13.452
I care about literacy.

00:17:13.452 --> 00:17:15.140
I care about numeracy.

00:17:15.140 --> 00:17:17.520
And I care about STEM.

00:17:17.520 --> 00:17:19.650
And even though I'm not
an engineer by training,

00:17:19.650 --> 00:17:22.950
I have a lot of the
basics, the fundamentals,

00:17:22.950 --> 00:17:29.720
of letter and number comfort
given to me through education.

00:17:29.720 --> 00:17:32.420
And that has allowed everything
that has come after this.

00:17:32.420 --> 00:17:33.480
This is cliche.

00:17:33.480 --> 00:17:35.480
But if you want to
teach people to fish

00:17:35.480 --> 00:17:38.120
and not just give
them a fish, you

00:17:38.120 --> 00:17:41.100
have to give them
the toolkit that

00:17:41.100 --> 00:17:43.560
allows them to be critical
problem solvers and creators.

00:17:43.560 --> 00:17:44.940
And you need to be literate.

00:17:44.940 --> 00:17:46.730
You need to have
numeracy for that.

00:17:46.730 --> 00:17:48.829
So what I would do
