because that's revealing of
the market's sort of appetite

00:28:14.392 --> 00:28:15.600
for those sorts of projects--

00:28:15.600 --> 00:28:18.160
TIM FERRISS: Can I-- I just
want to also just chime in here.

00:28:18.160 --> 00:28:20.450
Because there's something
that is sort of so

00:28:20.450 --> 00:28:23.126
intrinsic to your DNA that
sometimes people don't get it

00:28:23.126 --> 00:28:25.580
explicitly, which is they
vet all the products.

00:28:25.580 --> 00:28:31.270
So if a teacher is like, I
need a new huge, big screen TV.

00:28:31.270 --> 00:28:32.820
This Samsung would be ideal.

00:28:32.820 --> 00:28:34.571
Like, they look into
that, and make sure--

00:28:34.571 --> 00:28:35.945
OLIVER HURT-HILLER:
That's right.

